translated: The core of Hälsingborg, private at the apothecary in Sölvesborg since 1945. Captain in the Norrländska artillery regiment, reserve. Alf Robert, practicing physician in Varberg, born on November 8, 1902 in Varberg. Married in 1942 to Margit Stener. Children: Richard, born in 1944, Birgitta, born in 1946. Studied in Gothenburg until 1921, medical candidate in Stockholm until 1925, medical license in Lund until 1935. Trainee at the ear clinic in Lund in 1935, assistant physician at the eye clinic in 1936, trainee at the pediatric clinic in the same year, acting physician at the dermatology and venereology clinic in Malmö in the same year. Temporary appointment as a district physician in Alunda for two months in 1936. Temporary appointment as a city physician in Piteå in early 1936. Practicing physician in Varberg since 1937. Member of the board of the county hospital since 1946. Physician at the postal and Grimeton radio station. School physician at the secondary school and the municipal girls' school since 1945.
